    "id": "e0f3cdc2-4bfd-41dc-aacf-07f2d600136e",
    "sentence": "The, the, that part of it -- that part of it was irrelevant.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250129.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20250129",
    "context_question": "And, and five years ago, if I can paraphrase what you all decided, it was you’re going to not raise interest rates preemptively to, to head off inflation until you see sort of the whites of the eyes of inflation, because the solid labor market was so beneficial. Have the last few years changed your thinking about that?",
